# Parley Protocol Spec — CODEOWNERS
#
# Every file requires review by the repo owner. The normative protocol
# document is called out explicitly so that branch-protection rules
# requiring CODEOWNERS review gate every change to the spec itself
# (Adversarial F-020).
#
# IMPORTANT: CODEOWNERS alone does not enforce review. It only identifies
# who is notified. The two pieces that turn this into an actual control
# are configured at the GitHub UI level (Settings -> Branches -> main):
#
#   1. Require a pull request before merging.
#   2. Require review from Code Owners.
#   3. Required approvals: 1 (minimum; 2 preferred per cicd.std.md §3).
#   4. Dismiss stale reviews on new commits.
#   5. Require status check "CI Success" to pass.
#   6. Require signed commits.
#
# TODO(tim): configure the above rules on origin/main. See the
# companion note in README / a follow-up issue.

